1
00:00:00,136 --> 00:00:07,807
<i>There's you and me And all of the people with nothing to do</i>

2
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:12,690
<i>Nothing to lose and it's you and me</i>

3
00:00:15,125 --> 00:00:15,983
Damn.

4
00:00:19,936 --> 00:00:21,493
Toby! Stop!

5
00:01:23,145 --> 00:01:24,329
Cock-a-doodle-do.

6
00:01:26,036 --> 00:01:27,158
Cock-a-doodle who?

7
00:01:28,752 --> 00:01:29,972
Never mind.
I take that back.

8
00:01:30,023 --> 00:01:31,880
It's way too early for this kind of talk.

9
00:01:33,095 --> 00:01:35,318
Do you know that it's barely 5:00?

10
00:01:36,580 --> 00:01:37,285
I know.

11
00:01:40,477 --> 00:01:41,750
Is that a grocery list?

12
00:01:44,028 --> 00:01:44,728
Kind of.

13
00:01:44,779 --> 00:01:49,145
It's a list of things Ariel thinks she needs
for her slumber party tomorrow night.

14
00:01:49,534 --> 00:01:51,915
Rice cakes, sunflower seeds? What?

15
00:01:52,169 --> 00:01:54,341
Ariel's trying to make friends
with this girl named Celeste

16
00:01:54,392 --> 00:01:55,980
who is allergic to gluten.

17
00:01:58,801 --> 00:02:00,239
This is why you're up so early?

18
00:02:02,468 --> 00:02:03,226
No.

19
00:02:03,679 --> 00:02:05,164
I hit a girl with my car.

20
00:02:06,872 --> 00:02:08,045
In a dream.

21
00:02:08,877 --> 00:02:09,665
Okay.

22
00:02:12,844 --> 00:02:14,025
Was anyone else with you?

23
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:15,741
No.

24
00:02:16,832 --> 00:02:18,827
Was it nighttime, daytime?

25
00:02:19,041 --> 00:02:19,726
It was night.

26
00:02:21,663 --> 00:02:23,291
Any idea where the street might have been?

27
00:02:23,433 --> 00:02:24,680
What do you mean?
Like a name?

28
00:02:24,792 --> 00:02:26,117
A name would be good.

29
00:02:28,438 --> 00:02:30,688
Well, I remember
I felt like it was that area

30
00:02:31,636 --> 00:02:34,028
near the hospital
where all those houses are.

31
00:02:34,189 --> 00:02:35,408
Okay, this is easy.

32
00:02:35,923 --> 00:02:37,520
I'm glad you feel so relieved.

33
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:40,202
Let's just agree,
from now until the end of time,

34
00:02:40,847 --> 00:02:42,400
that you don't drive alone at night

35
00:02:42,451 --> 00:02:45,414
in that area by the hospital
where the houses are.

36
00:02:47,501 --> 00:02:48,687
What? You're upset?

37
00:02:48,738 --> 00:02:50,422
I'm just frustrated. That's all.

38
00:02:50,473 --> 00:02:51,295
Why?

39
00:02:52,276 --> 00:02:54,339
We've been at this for a while now.

40
00:02:54,688 --> 00:02:55,435
And?

41
00:02:55,685 --> 00:02:56,767
All this skepticism.

42
00:02:56,818 --> 00:02:57,971
This isn't skepticism.

43
00:02:58,756 --> 00:03:00,796
This is the exact opposite of skepticism.

44
00:03:01,175 --> 00:03:03,403
This is absolute conviction followed by--

45
00:03:03,454 --> 00:03:04,906
and this is the important part--

46
00:03:04,956 --> 00:03:07,227
by completely logical plan of action.

47
00:03:07,278 --> 00:03:08,004
Really?

48
00:03:08,055 --> 00:03:08,773
Truly.

49
00:03:08,824 --> 00:03:09,500
It's like that joke.

50
00:03:09,551 --> 00:03:11,307
The guy walks in to the doctor's office, he says, "Hey, Doc,

51
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:14,536
"my arm hurts when I raise it like this." And the doctor says,

52
00:03:14,691 --> 00:03:16,206
"Fine. Don't raise it like that."

53
00:03:16,966 --> 00:03:18,799
We can't stop the night from coming,

54
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:21,421
we can't stop the girl from stepping out into the road.

55
00:03:21,472 --> 00:03:23,414
But if you're not in the road in your car,

56
00:03:23,465 --> 00:03:24,478
you're not gonna hit her.

57
00:03:24,885 --> 00:03:26,477
Allison, smile,
for God's sake.

58
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:29,052
This is a tragedy we can absolutely avoid.

59
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,372
This is a gift.

60
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:32,372
Now I say we celebrate...

61
00:03:33,624 --> 00:03:34,544
back in bed.

62
00:03:40,471 --> 00:03:41,678
Would you like me to check your oil?

63
00:03:42,259 --> 00:03:43,173
You're kidding me.

64
00:03:43,224 --> 00:03:44,406
You guys still do that?

65
00:03:44,815 --> 00:03:46,545
Well, you're at the full service island, Miss.

66
00:03:48,593 --> 00:03:49,643
Damn it.

67
00:03:51,232 --> 00:03:52,494
So would you like me to check something?

68
00:03:53,826 --> 00:03:54,869
I don't know, no.

69
00:03:55,761 --> 00:03:56,656
Oh, wait a second.

70
00:04:04,634 --> 00:04:05,234
Morning.

71
00:04:05,486 --> 00:04:07,690
Morning. I'm not sure if you're even open yet,

72
00:04:07,741 --> 00:04:10,926
but, uh, I was just hoping to get a cup of coffee

73
00:04:10,977 --> 00:04:13,272
while they put in a new headlight for me across the street.

74
00:04:13,323 --> 00:04:14,433
Yeah, right this way.

75
00:04:52,584 --> 00:04:53,577
Stop it.

76
00:04:57,468 --> 00:04:58,356
Thank you.

77
00:05:15,428 --> 00:05:16,566
James?

78
00:05:23,951 --> 00:05:24,915
James!

79
00:05:31,547 --> 00:05:32,414
Nadine.

80
00:05:34,079 --> 00:05:35,062
What are you doing?

81
00:05:37,636 --> 00:05:38,954
Did you call the broker?

82
00:05:40,492 --> 00:05:42,402
No, I did not call the broker.

83
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:47,241
It just did it again in the bathroom.

84
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:49,222
Nadine.

85
00:05:50,584 --> 00:05:53,474
There's no water and the lights flickered on and off.

86
00:05:53,904 --> 00:05:55,222
It is an old house.

87
00:06:02,934 --> 00:06:04,057
There's water now.

88
00:06:07,034 --> 00:06:07,985
There's water.

89
00:06:12,523 --> 00:06:13,890
I want to move.

90
00:06:15,831 --> 00:06:17,536
Nadine, please.

91
00:06:19,058 --> 00:06:20,916
I can't live like this, James.

92
00:06:22,608 --> 00:06:23,764
I just...

93
00:06:25,396 --> 00:06:26,334
I can't.

94
00:06:32,459 --> 00:06:34,435
I think I need to tell someone.

95
00:06:41,079 --> 00:06:42,563
Tell someone what exactly?

96
00:06:46,019 --> 00:06:47,164
Tell someone what?

97
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:56,592
Tell someone what?

98
00:07:00,591 --> 00:07:02,394
Tell someone what?!

99
00:07:02,445 --> 00:07:03,191
What?!

100
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:04,848
Here you go.

101
00:07:07,139 --> 00:07:08,538
Oh, thank you.

102
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:27,867
Pardon me.

103
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:29,740
I don't mean to trouble you,

104
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:32,508
but would you mind if I stole some of your artificial sweetener?

105
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:34,309
Excuse me?

106
00:07:35,008 --> 00:07:35,850
Sweetener.

107
00:07:35,901 --> 00:07:37,634
I don't have any at my table.

108
00:07:41,613 --> 00:07:42,543
Thank you.

109
00:07:42,594 --> 00:07:43,530
Sure.

110
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:50,393
Was there something else?

111
00:07:52,376 --> 00:07:53,613
Are you all right?

112
00:07:56,521 --> 00:07:58,365
I'm sorry. I don't mean to pry.

113
00:07:58,416 --> 00:07:59,419
It's just...

114
00:08:02,939 --> 00:08:03,615
You know what?

115
00:08:06,188 --> 00:08:07,707
In case you change your mind.

116
00:08:11,809 --> 00:08:13,348
The District Attorney's office?

117
00:08:15,465 --> 00:08:17,711
Crying in public against the law?

118
00:08:18,314 --> 00:08:20,767
No, no, of course not.

119
00:08:22,278 --> 00:08:23,308
I'm sorry.

120
00:08:23,801 --> 00:08:24,881
You're trying to be nice,

121
00:08:24,932 --> 00:08:26,356
and I'm not playing along.

122
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:29,826
Let me pay for your coffee.

123
00:08:29,877 --> 00:08:31,413
No, no, no.
You don't have to do that.

124
00:08:31,546 --> 00:08:32,889
But I'd like to.

125
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,577
Well, it's my birthday in a couple of days.

126
00:08:36,570 --> 00:08:39,751
I'd like to do something nice for somebody.

127
00:08:43,316 --> 00:08:44,560
Enjoy your coffee.

128
00:08:47,043 --> 00:08:49,372
Try not to trip on the sugar when you sit back down.

129
00:08:51,693 --> 00:08:54,944
All I'm saying is I should have gotten her name, that's all.

130
00:08:54,995 --> 00:08:56,321
It was stupid of me.

131
00:08:57,506 --> 00:08:59,209
What would you have done if you had gotten her name?

132
00:08:59,569 --> 00:09:00,622
I don't know.

133
00:09:00,723 --> 00:09:02,293
Run it through the computer at work.

134
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,041
See if there was ever a police report,

135
00:09:04,092 --> 00:09:06,411
see if she ever filed a restraining order.

136
00:09:06,462 --> 00:09:07,539
Did you get tofu?

137
00:09:08,116 --> 00:09:08,952
I got it.

138
00:09:09,396 --> 00:09:10,201
Tofu?

139
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:12,513
Celeste likes it on her pizza.

140
00:09:13,006 --> 00:09:13,721
Yum.

141
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,152
Who's this Celeste?

142
00:09:15,203 --> 00:09:17,765
I don't remember you ever having mentioned her before.

143
00:09:17,819 --> 00:09:19,159
She's a new girl at school.

144
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:20,633
Her family just moved here from New York.

145
00:09:20,684 --> 00:09:22,106
I really like her.

146
00:09:22,316 --> 00:09:25,505
She's traveled everywhere and knows everything about everything.

147
00:09:31,102 --> 00:09:31,896
Hello?

148
00:09:31,989 --> 00:09:34,125
Allison, it's Lee Scanlon.
Did I wake you?

149
00:09:34,456 --> 00:09:35,355
It's okay.

150
00:09:35,969 --> 00:09:37,651
Do you know somebody named Nadine Massey?

151
00:09:38,529 --> 00:09:39,791
Nadine Massey.

152
00:09:40,031 --> 00:09:41,795
No, never heard of her.

153
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:43,651
She's not a friend of yours,

154
00:09:43,702 --> 00:09:44,892
someone you met through work, maybe?

155
00:09:45,424 --> 00:09:46,444
I don't think so.

156
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:50,130
Any idea why she might have your business card?

157
00:09:51,231 --> 00:09:53,961
Wait, yeah, I might have met her yesterday.

158
00:09:54,012 --> 00:09:55,344
What's going on? Is she okay?

159
00:09:56,626 --> 00:09:58,607
"Okay" is not an adjective I'd use, no.

160
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:07,315
So their names are Hannah,

161
00:10:07,366 --> 00:10:08,884
Celeste and Ashley.

162
00:10:09,457 --> 00:10:10,509
No, I know Hannah.

163
00:10:11,078 --> 00:10:14,396
They're not due here till 3:00, and I will absolutely be back before then,

164
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:15,274
so don't worry.

165
00:10:15,325 --> 00:10:16,579
I believe you.

166
00:10:17,305 --> 00:10:18,492
I need to know if it's her.

167
00:10:19,591 --> 00:10:20,465
No, I know.

168
00:10:21,132 --> 00:10:22,468
Like I was supposed to meet her,

169
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:24,463
like I was supposed to help her,
and I didn't.

170
00:10:24,970 --> 00:10:26,172
Al, give yourself a break.

171
00:10:26,223 --> 00:10:28,378
You only met this woman for five minutes.

172
00:10:29,101 --> 00:10:30,060
I know.

173
00:10:32,034 --> 00:10:34,644
Husband says he fell asleep on the sofa watching television.

174
00:10:35,678 --> 00:10:37,241
When he woke up around 3:00 and went to the bedroom,

175
00:10:37,292 --> 00:10:38,936
he found his wife dead on the floor.

176
00:10:38,987 --> 00:10:40,431
Gunshot wound to the right temple.

177
00:10:40,645 --> 00:10:42,107
He didn't hear the gunshot?

178
00:10:42,506 --> 00:10:43,445
That's what he says.

179
00:10:43,943 --> 00:10:46,404
Terrace doors were open, but there's no sign of an intruder.

180
00:10:47,719 --> 00:10:49,102
The gun was on the floor next to her.

181
00:10:49,153 --> 00:10:51,280
Husband says that he kept it in the bedroom safe.

182
00:10:51,787 --> 00:10:53,674
Guy says he loved his wife like the dickens.

183
00:10:54,091 --> 00:10:55,962
That she was admittedly the high-strung type,

184
00:10:56,013 --> 00:10:56,943
prone to hysteria.

185
00:10:57,537 --> 00:11:00,481
He seems devastated but not all that surprised she decided to end it all.

186
00:11:01,539 --> 00:11:03,001
You don't seem so convinced.

187
00:11:03,294 --> 00:11:04,044
I don't know.

188
00:11:05,686 --> 00:11:08,022
I guess I'm a little surprised she'd choose to use a gun when there's

189
00:11:08,073 --> 00:11:10,382
enough tranquilizers in the house to take down Shamu.

190
00:11:12,928 --> 00:11:14,480
Want to hear something really strange?

191
00:11:17,109 --> 00:11:18,465
The last few days,

192
00:11:19,239 --> 00:11:20,772
she actually seemed happy.

193
00:11:22,755 --> 00:11:23,589
Happy?

194
00:11:24,304 --> 00:11:25,088
Well...

195
00:11:26,203 --> 00:11:27,731
I mean, happier than she'd been...

196
00:11:29,012 --> 00:11:30,000
in a long time.

197
00:11:33,885 --> 00:11:35,932
At least it seemed that way to me.
I don't know.

198
00:11:38,847 --> 00:11:40,200
Maybe it was actually relief.

199
00:11:42,908 --> 00:11:44,025
Making the decision...

200
00:11:45,772 --> 00:11:46,374
knowing...

201
00:11:47,942 --> 00:11:49,414
that it'll all be over soon.

202
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:08,242
I appreciate you taking the time to speak with us.

203
00:12:10,975 --> 00:12:13,669
May have to speak with you again in the next few days.

204
00:12:14,121 --> 00:12:15,316
By all means, Detective.

205
00:12:17,574 --> 00:12:19,174
Daddy, what beats two pairs?

206
00:12:19,326 --> 00:12:20,399
Uh, three of a kind.

207
00:12:20,450 --> 00:12:21,537
Hey, hey, you.

208
00:12:23,523 --> 00:12:24,582
Who wants popcorn?

209
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:26,601
Oh, I do,
I do, I do!

210
00:12:27,203 --> 00:12:28,352
- Want popcorn?
- Yeah.

211
00:12:28,771 --> 00:12:29,764
Thank you very much.

212
00:12:30,075 --> 00:12:31,827
Daddy, what beats three of a kind?

213
00:12:31,878 --> 00:12:33,231
A full house.

214
00:12:33,517 --> 00:12:34,546
I see your melon.

215
00:12:34,597 --> 00:12:35,987
I'll raise you a cherry.

216
00:12:36,287 --> 00:12:38,313
Wait, you've got a full house?

217
00:12:38,717 --> 00:12:39,624
I quit.

218
00:12:39,851 --> 00:12:42,044
Fold, Celeste.
You mean you fold.

219
00:12:42,140 --> 00:12:43,483
Yeah, I fold, too.

220
00:12:43,788 --> 00:12:45,908
Okay, uh, anybody else need anything?

221
00:12:45,961 --> 00:12:46,782
Everybody okay?

222
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:48,188
No, we're okay.

223
00:12:48,239 --> 00:12:48,839
All right.

224
00:12:48,813 --> 00:12:51,911
So we're heading back to the bedroom for a hot game of Hungry Hungry Hippos.

225
00:12:52,085 --> 00:12:53,678
Hungry Hungry Hippos!

226
00:12:53,867 --> 00:12:55,972
Um, holler if you need me to float you a loan.

227
00:12:56,023 --> 00:12:56,932
Yes, Daddy.

228
00:12:57,217 --> 00:12:58,366
Thanks,
Mr. Dubois.

229
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:01,845
This is no fun.
You always win.

230
00:13:03,081 --> 00:13:04,605
Well, I'm sorry.
I can't help it.

231
00:13:05,093 --> 00:13:06,031
She's just lucky.

232
00:13:06,140 --> 00:13:06,848
That's all.

233
00:13:07,428 --> 00:13:11,165
Well, I want to do something else, something fun.

234
00:13:11,780 --> 00:13:14,222
You don't have a swimming pool or an X-box or anything.

235
00:13:14,273 --> 00:13:15,638
Your house is no fun.

236
00:13:16,644 --> 00:13:18,286
Well, I'm sorry.

237
00:13:18,519 --> 00:13:20,645
It's okay. You can't help that you're boring.

238
00:13:23,282 --> 00:13:25,465
Well, how about we play...

239
00:13:25,916 --> 00:13:27,160
Tomorrows?

240
00:13:28,445 --> 00:13:29,681
Tomorrows?

241
00:13:30,639 --> 00:13:31,342
Oh, God,

242
00:13:31,554 --> 00:13:33,109
she's really good at this.

243
00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:36,479
Three of diamonds.

244
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:38,641
That's a good card.

245
00:13:39,293 --> 00:13:40,417
A lucky card.

246
00:13:41,538 --> 00:13:43,615
There's a boy you like.

247
00:13:45,684 --> 00:13:46,727
Robert...

248
00:13:47,516 --> 00:13:48,583
Bobby...

249
00:13:48,634 --> 00:13:49,815
Bobby Soames?

250
00:13:51,024 --> 00:13:52,221
He'll call you tomorrow.

251
00:13:52,688 --> 00:13:53,728
Who's Bobby Soames?

252
00:13:54,275 --> 00:13:55,799
He's a friend of my brother's.

253
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:58,142
He doesn't even go to our school.

254
00:13:58,363 --> 00:13:59,304
How did you know?

255
00:13:59,688 --> 00:14:00,315
I told you,

256
00:14:00,366 --> 00:14:01,459
she's really good at this.

257
00:14:01,753 --> 00:14:02,516
Do me. Do me.

258
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:03,195
Okay.

259
00:14:06,051 --> 00:14:07,204
Five of spades.

260
00:14:07,918 --> 00:14:09,365
Not so lucky.

261
00:14:10,452 --> 00:14:11,110
What?

262
00:14:13,316 --> 00:14:15,175
Something's going to happento your left ankle.

263
00:14:17,518 --> 00:14:19,117
What are you talking about?

264
00:14:20,056 --> 00:14:21,024
Maybe I'm wrong.

265
00:14:21,382 --> 00:14:22,517
I don't know.

266
00:14:22,726 --> 00:14:24,300
You knew about Bobby Soames.

267
00:14:25,141 --> 00:14:26,448
I'd stay off that ankle.

268
00:14:28,628 --> 00:14:29,680
Okay, my turn.

269
00:14:30,401 --> 00:14:31,167
Wait a second.

270
00:14:31,769 --> 00:14:32,767
I'm the new friend.

271
00:14:33,196 --> 00:14:35,194
I'm the guest. Do me again.

272
00:14:41,660 --> 00:14:42,507
The queen of hearts.

273
00:14:42,816 --> 00:14:43,599
I like that one.

274
00:14:46,535 --> 00:14:47,438
What's the matter?

275
00:14:48,774 --> 00:14:50,074
