540
00:29:43,643 --> 00:29:44,874
speedy a resolve as possible.

541
00:29:45,983 --> 00:29:46,909
Unfortunately,

542
00:29:47,795 --> 00:29:52,304
there was a firearm registered in your name that was involved with your

543
00:29:52,355 --> 00:29:53,741
late wife's death.

544
00:29:53,881 --> 00:29:55,802
I understand.

545
00:29:56,251 --> 00:29:57,313
You can ask me anything.

546
00:29:58,681 --> 00:29:59,529
I'm sorry.

547
00:29:59,861 --> 00:30:00,672
Bit of a cold.

548
00:30:00,950 --> 00:30:01,859
That's fine.

549
00:30:03,254 --> 00:30:06,877
I know that both the detective and Mrs. Dubois have asked you this,

550
00:30:07,852 --> 00:30:12,470
but do you think there was something specific that precipitated your late

551
00:30:12,521 --> 00:30:14,534
wife's desire to take her own life?

552
00:30:19,460 --> 00:30:20,688
I've racked my brain.

553
00:30:20,739 --> 00:30:21,590
I, um...

554
00:30:24,177 --> 00:30:25,402
Her birthday was coming up.

555
00:30:26,568 --> 00:30:29,943
But she was always pretty excited about that.

556
00:30:31,424 --> 00:30:33,989
You ever own a green 2004 ES, Mr. Massie?

557
00:30:37,366 --> 00:30:38,100
I did.

558
00:30:39,930 --> 00:30:40,742
Um, it was stolen.

559
00:30:41,450 --> 00:30:44,107
We have witnesses that possibly put it at the scene of a hit-and-run.

560
00:30:46,815 --> 00:30:52,525
Okay. Um... well, I mean it was stolen...

561
00:30:54,118 --> 00:30:54,935
a while ago.

562
00:30:55,495 --> 00:30:59,254
I think, uh, it's been almost a year now.

563
00:30:59,954 --> 00:31:00,774
We understand that,

564
00:31:00,825 --> 00:31:03,815
but this, this hit-and-run I'm referring to

565
00:31:03,866 --> 00:31:05,862
actually occurred a couple of days before that.

566
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,307
Your wife's birthday, actually.

567
00:31:11,111 --> 00:31:12,204
15-year-old girl,

568
00:31:12,325 --> 00:31:13,733
Melanie Davenport, was killed.

569
00:31:14,346 --> 00:31:16,046
She was running after her dog.

570
00:31:17,084 --> 00:31:19,051
The person who hit her just kept going.

571
00:31:19,928 --> 00:31:21,618
Didn't even call 911.

572
00:31:30,059 --> 00:31:30,736
Okay.

573
00:31:34,082 --> 00:31:37,815
So... the reason I'm here,

574
00:31:39,686 --> 00:31:40,351
I mean...

575
00:31:41,771 --> 00:31:43,104
what you're trying to tell me...

576
00:31:45,898 --> 00:31:52,384
You think that maybe my wife hit this girl in our car and never reported it?

577
00:31:56,697 --> 00:31:57,297
Well...

578
00:31:57,246 --> 00:31:59,443
Because... I mean,

579
00:31:59,872 --> 00:32:00,767
if that were true,

580
00:32:02,579 --> 00:32:06,143
it would certainly explain a lot of things.

581
00:32:07,734 --> 00:32:08,655
What things?

582
00:32:11,202 --> 00:32:12,829
Well, uh...

583
00:32:14,581 --> 00:32:18,181
Nadine's state of mind over this entire past year,

584
00:32:18,232 --> 00:32:18,897
for one.

585
00:32:21,196 --> 00:32:22,580
If this were true, and mind you,

586
00:32:22,631 --> 00:32:25,265
I'm not saying that this is,

587
00:32:25,316 --> 00:32:30,629
but... I can't even imagine what kind of...

588
00:32:32,263 --> 00:32:34,521
terrible guilt she must have been living with.

589
00:32:39,478 --> 00:32:41,457
I mean, it's no wonder she was so unstrung.

590
00:32:49,424 --> 00:32:50,760
Everyone's in bed.

591
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:54,915
I lied and told them you'd sneak in later
while they were asleep and give them kisses.

592
00:32:55,845 --> 00:32:57,792
It's not necessarily a lie.

593
00:32:58,189 --> 00:32:59,411
How do you know it's a lie?

594
00:32:59,845 --> 00:33:01,070
I'm a student of history.

595
00:33:01,902 --> 00:33:04,323
And history suggests that when you get in one of these moods,

596
00:33:05,812 --> 00:33:08,910
the kind where you end up laying here on the couch stewing in your

597
00:33:08,961 --> 00:33:11,390
inability to effect any real change,

598
00:33:12,600 --> 00:33:16,129
eventually you fall asleep and no one sees you till morning.

599
00:33:17,542 --> 00:33:18,535
It's not going to happen.

600
00:33:19,148 --> 00:33:22,646
I just need a little time for myself, okay?

601
00:33:25,754 --> 00:33:27,146
I had a very depressing day.

602
00:33:28,488 --> 00:33:29,217
Well, I wouldn't know.

603
00:33:29,268 --> 00:33:31,979
You haven't said three words to me since I got home.

604
00:33:32,259 --> 00:33:34,012
Here are the highlights:
James Massie--

605
00:33:34,134 --> 00:33:36,749
he completely sold out his poor dead wife today.

606
00:33:37,619 --> 00:33:39,283
He could have said he didn't know anything.

607
00:33:39,908 --> 00:33:41,502
He knows we can't prove he was there.

608
00:33:42,144 --> 00:33:44,143
But no, he had to go that extra step

609
00:33:44,816 --> 00:33:47,835
and offer up Nadine who is not in a position to defend herself.

610
00:33:49,971 --> 00:33:52,751
I'm sorry. I just have to get that out of my system.

611
00:33:53,358 --> 00:33:55,157
Well, I have something I have to get out of my system.

612
00:33:56,041 --> 00:34:00,147
I asked Ariel for Celeste's parents' names and phone number today.

613
00:34:01,644 --> 00:34:02,622
I'm a scientist.

614
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:04,325
People don't fall suddenly ill.

615
00:34:04,376 --> 00:34:06,428
It happens gradually over time.

616
00:34:07,099 --> 00:34:09,594
And there are windows of opportunity in which to intervene.

617
00:34:11,219 --> 00:34:15,419
I think it's worth the risk and any possible hardship to say something.

618
00:34:16,142 --> 00:34:18,473
And I don't think I could live with myself if I didn't.

619
00:34:20,780 --> 00:34:21,722
I know.

620
00:34:26,799 --> 00:34:27,945
I'll see you in the morning.

621
00:34:29,490 --> 00:34:30,480
Don't worry.

622
00:34:30,531 --> 00:34:32,172
I'm not going to fall asleep out here.

623
00:34:32,405 --> 00:34:33,134
Ha.

624
00:34:33,802 --> 00:34:34,402
Ha.

625
00:34:35,864 --> 00:34:36,464
Ha.

626
00:34:41,501 --> 00:34:43,489
<i>Did you ever see a dream romancing</i>

627
00:34:43,540 --> 00:34:46,280
<i>Well I did</i>

628
00:34:46,857 --> 00:34:50,719
<i>Did you ever see heaven right in your arms</i>

629
00:34:50,926 --> 00:34:52,076
James! James!

630
00:34:55,869 --> 00:34:56,904
Nadine!

631
00:34:59,799 --> 00:35:00,907
Oh, God.

632
00:35:01,407 --> 00:35:02,160
Baby.

633
00:35:04,202 --> 00:35:05,014
What did you do?

634
00:35:05,190 --> 00:35:05,839
Oh...

635
00:35:09,340 --> 00:35:10,325
Don't worry, honey.

636
00:35:10,799 --> 00:35:12,809
I'm going to get you some help, okay?

637
00:35:15,875 --> 00:35:16,622
James.

638
00:35:17,343 --> 00:35:17,943
James.

639
00:35:19,334 --> 00:35:20,493
We have to tell.

640
00:35:21,899 --> 00:35:23,120
I can't go on.

641
00:35:24,370 --> 00:35:25,717
I can't live this way.

642
00:35:28,252 --> 00:35:29,824
What are you talking about?
Tell who?

643
00:35:30,593 --> 00:35:31,826
The police.

644
00:35:33,327 --> 00:35:35,347
She'll never leave until we do.

645
00:35:46,397 --> 00:35:49,359
<i>Did you ever see a dream walking?</i>

646
00:35:49,622 --> 00:35:55,762
<i>Well I did.
Did you ever hear a dream talking?</i>

647
00:35:56,210 --> 00:36:00,881
<i>Well I did.
Did you ever have a dream...</i>

648
00:36:08,855 --> 00:36:09,896
Did you call them?

649
00:36:10,761 --> 00:36:11,431
Are they coming?

650
00:36:11,482 --> 00:36:12,142
They're coming.

651
00:36:12,983 --> 00:36:13,957
You're going to be fine.

652
00:36:17,294 --> 00:36:18,258
This was stupid,

653
00:36:18,329 --> 00:36:19,548
what I did.

654
00:36:21,659 --> 00:36:22,919
I don't want to die.

655
00:36:23,074 --> 00:36:23,859
I know.

656
00:36:24,234 --> 00:36:25,566
I just wanted it to stop.

657
00:36:25,979 --> 00:36:26,886
Shh.

658
00:36:31,548 --> 00:36:32,364
Will you stay with me?

659
00:36:33,553 --> 00:36:37,546
I will. I'll stay with you till they get here.

660
00:36:40,291 --> 00:36:41,823
Close your eyes, baby.

661
00:36:42,309 --> 00:36:43,128
It's all right.

662
00:36:48,006 --> 00:36:49,782
It's going to be just a few minutes.

663
00:36:52,591 --> 00:36:53,490
Shh.

664
00:37:01,977 --> 00:37:02,872
Allison?

665
00:37:03,417 --> 00:37:04,017
It's okay.

666
00:37:04,006 --> 00:37:04,977
It's just me.

667
00:37:05,109 --> 00:37:05,893
I need to get my wallet.

668
00:37:05,944 --> 00:37:06,964
I have to go for a drive.

669
00:37:07,518 --> 00:37:08,284
A drive?

670
00:37:09,559 --> 00:37:10,316
It's 2:00 in the morning.

671
00:37:10,367 --> 00:37:11,715
Where in the world are you going to drive to?

672
00:37:11,911 --> 00:37:12,823
I need to go to that street,

673
00:37:12,874 --> 00:37:13,859
the one near the hospital.

674
00:37:13,910 --> 00:37:15,036
This isn't over, not yet.

675
00:37:15,087 --> 00:37:16,382
I just had another dream.

676
00:37:17,007 --> 00:37:18,852
Well, fine, then get back in bed, dream some more.

677
00:37:18,903 --> 00:37:19,659
No, I can't.

678
00:37:19,888 --> 00:37:20,569
That dead girl,

679
00:37:20,634 --> 00:37:21,537
Melanie Davenport,

680
00:37:21,658 --> 00:37:23,214
I think she's trying to tell me something.

681
00:37:41,126 --> 00:37:42,718
You're not going to find her here.

682
00:37:46,591 --> 00:37:49,032
Melanie's fine. She's safe.

683
00:37:50,081 --> 00:37:52,855
She's where she's supposed to be finally.

684
00:37:54,109 --> 00:37:55,079
And how about you?

685
00:37:55,741 --> 00:37:56,433
Me?

686
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:59,420
I'm still adjusting.

687
00:38:00,569 --> 00:38:02,823
Getting... used to the idea.

688
00:38:04,765 --> 00:38:06,412
Trying to accept what he did.

689
00:38:13,055 --> 00:38:16,255
You know, it took me almost 27 minutes to die.

690
00:38:18,305 --> 00:38:23,584
He sat beside me holding my hand for 27 minutes while I tried to hang on,

691
00:38:26,446 --> 00:38:28,565
listening for the sirens that never came.

692
00:38:32,549 --> 00:38:34,039
But I guess I had it coming.

693
00:38:36,911 --> 00:38:41,122
I should have come forward to the police and told them what we'd done.

694
00:38:42,312 --> 00:38:43,855
That's all that Melanie wanted.

695
00:38:44,995 --> 00:38:46,238
She never meant to hurt me.

696
00:38:48,690 --> 00:38:50,642
That day that you and I met in the restaurant--

697
00:38:52,117 --> 00:38:53,672
she arranged that you know.

698
00:38:55,452 --> 00:38:56,874
And the business with your headlight?

699
00:38:58,241 --> 00:39:01,950
She was giving me a chance to confess, a chance to live,

700
00:39:02,001 --> 00:39:03,117
and I didn't take it.

701
00:39:06,084 --> 00:39:09,617
And now Melanie's parents will never know who took their child from them.

702
00:39:12,677 --> 00:39:13,915
And what happens to your husband?

703
00:39:15,804 --> 00:39:17,278
He had a chance, too.

704
00:39:18,730 --> 00:39:20,203
Today, with you, in the room,

705
00:39:21,067 --> 00:39:22,186
he had a chance,

706
00:39:22,644 --> 00:39:23,811
and he didn't take it.

707
00:39:28,514 --> 00:39:30,023
So now, I guess it's up to me.

708
00:39:32,619 --> 00:39:34,620
I don't understand.
What are you going to do?

709
00:39:35,429 --> 00:39:37,187
Obviously,
he's not afraid of ghosts.

710
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:40,756
He's not afraid of flickering lights or music.

711
00:39:42,425 --> 00:39:44,432
But if someone, or something,

712
00:39:46,492 --> 00:39:50,434
was to blow out the pilot light in the old stove in our kitchen,

713
00:39:52,403 --> 00:39:54,039
and James were to have a cold,

714
00:39:55,343 --> 00:39:56,603
not smell the gas,

715
00:39:57,967 --> 00:40:02,205
let it fill the room and James were to light a cigarette...

716
00:40:06,500 --> 00:40:08,810
I wonder what those sirens are all about?

717
00:40:14,983 --> 00:40:16,221
Do you smell something?

718
00:40:30,958 --> 00:40:32,789
Don't forget to bring home those names and that phone number.

719
00:40:33,017 --> 00:40:33,766
I won't, Daddy.

720
00:40:33,980 --> 00:40:34,580
Okay.

721
00:40:36,703 --> 00:40:37,704
Why isn't Mommy up?

722
00:40:38,289 --> 00:40:39,896
I like the way she pours better.

723
00:40:40,105 --> 00:40:42,755
Mommy was out late last night doing some emergency work.

724
00:40:44,027 --> 00:40:44,870
Darn.

725
00:40:47,370 --> 00:40:48,104
Hello?

726
00:40:51,051 --> 00:40:52,846
Yes, this is her mother.

727
00:40:54,527 --> 00:40:55,182
Morning.

728
00:40:59,483 --> 00:41:00,627
What about Celeste?

729
00:41:00,678 --> 00:41:02,157
Uh, I already reminded her.

730
00:41:02,450 --> 00:41:03,953
Well, that was her mom just now.

731
00:41:05,034 --> 00:41:07,781
She was wondering if you could pick up Celeste's homework today because

732
00:41:07,832 --> 00:41:10,517
Celeste needs to go to New York for a couple of days.

733
00:41:12,075 --> 00:41:13,663
Why, what's going on?

734
00:41:14,420 --> 00:41:15,768
I guess she has a cousin,

735
00:41:17,071 --> 00:41:19,911
a spitting image of Celeste,
only ten years older,

736
00:41:20,286 --> 00:41:22,695
and I guess she was just diagnosed with leukemia,

737
00:41:22,751 --> 00:41:24,647
so they're all going there to say good-bye.

738
00:41:31,291 --> 00:41:33,746
You know what?
I'm not hungry anymore.

739
00:41:33,797 --> 00:41:35,782
I'm just going to go to my room.

740
00:41:40,972 --> 00:41:42,809
I owe that girl a conversation.

741
00:41:45,378 --> 00:41:46,304
I don't get it.

742
00:41:46,355 --> 00:41:47,356
What's going on?

743
00:41:47,688 --> 00:41:49,609
Why is everybody so serious?

744
00:41:50,638 --> 00:41:52,028
It's hard to explain.

745
00:41:53,412 --> 00:41:54,971
You'll see, the older you get.

746
00:41:56,127 --> 00:41:57,035
I'll be right back.

747
00:42:00,471 --> 00:42:02,983
Well, I don't know how to tell this to you.

748
00:42:04,505 --> 00:42:06,858
I guess it's just you and me, kid.

749
00:42:07,150 --> 00:42:10,428
